unittitle_ssm: Adolf Gundersen Oral History Interview of Murray Bookchin
abstract_ssm: The Adolf Gundersen Oral History Interview of Murray Bookchin consists of a 10-audio cassette interview with political theorist Murray Bookchin by political scientist Adolf G. Gundersen. The interview was conducted over a period of five days from August 22-26 1995. In the interview Bookchin discusses events of his life, his books and the development of his political theory. Murray Bookchin (1921-2006) was a social theorist and political philosopher who is most well-known for his theories on ecology and his role in founding the social ecology movement.
